{
  "stem": "21013.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I wrote five letters telling them that I hope that they know the situation in Austria, that I was a Jewish girl, that I had good grades in school and that I was healthy, and I need help.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "All I need is an affidavit of support.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I don't need any money.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I have enough money for fare and I have enough clothes and that I won't bother them or be a burden to them, but I need an affidavit of support in order to get a visa and the permission to come to the United States.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And by return mail, I had three affidavits, which was a-- nothing short of a miracle.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And they either thought that we were really related or manufactured a relationship for the benefit of the United States State Department.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And it became like a re-unification of a family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I then had a visa and an affidavit to come to the United States.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "However, the quota number was so high that I had to wait and I couldn't actually get the permit to leave.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I had to wait 'til my quota number was up.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And I would have had to wait so long it would have been too late.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I forced my way into the consulate in Vienna after standing in line all night long, and-- something like 14 hours.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And by that time, I was so overwrought that I screamed at the man who was at the door and pushed him aside and ran up the stairs and got into a room and started to cry.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And a woman came in and asked me why I was crying.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And it's a long story, but she happened to be the wife of the General Consul of the American-- of the United States.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
